      <h1 class='title'>Defence Bills Agency</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c222WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_222ws' title='Col. 222WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c222WS' name='column_222ws' href='#column_222ws' rel='bookmark'>222WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-05971'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_61'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-angus-robertson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_61' title='Link to this speech by Mr Angus Robertson' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-angus-robertson" title="Mr Angus Robertson">Angus Robertson</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-05971">To ask the Secretary of State for Defence what the total spending was of the Defence Bills Agency for the last year for which figures are available; and how much of that was spent in Scotland. [86061]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-05972'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_62'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-adam-ingram' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_62' title='Link to this speech by Mr Adam Ingram' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-adam-ingram" title="Mr Adam Ingram">Mr. Ingram</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-05972"> [<span class="italic">holding answer 10 December 2002</span>]: The total value of Defence contractors' bills settled by the Defence Bills Agency for the year ending 31 March 2002 was &#x00A3;16,849 billion. Data on how much of this figure was spent in Scotland or any United Kingdom region is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
